                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, June 22: Bank of Rajasthan (BoR) is seeking legal opinion on the unofficial meeting that shareholders of the bank held yesterday where they passed a resolution approving its merger with ICICI Bank. The extraordinary general meeting called by the management had been stayed by a Calcutta court, but shareholders who had congregated in Mumbai went ahead and approved the merger.                             
	 Berlin, June 22: Britain, France and Germany today committed to levying a fee on banks to shield taxpayers from the cost of resolving financial crises. Meanwhile, the British government unveiled an emergency budget with a steep hike in taxes and a slew of spending cuts.                            
	 New Delhi, June 22: The State Bank of India is understood to be raising $1 billion from overseas markets through bonds, for which it has appointed six lead arrangers
                                                                                                                          
